assessments.issue: The re.MULTILINE flag is redundant when checking individual stripped lines since ^ already matches at the start of the string
assessments.action: Removed the redundant re.MULTILINE flag from the per-line re.search() calls in apps/api/plane/utils/html_processor.py lines 307, 309, 310, and 313. The flag is not needed since we're checking individual lines that have already been stripped, so ^ already matches the start of the string.

assessments.issue: review-output.json and revision-response.json are included in the commit but appear to be temporary review/process files
assessments.action: Removed review-output.json, revision-response.json, and .code-review-output.json from the repository. These temporary review files should not be committed.

summary: Addressed both minor code review issues: (1) Removed redundant re.MULTILINE flags from per-line regex searches in html_processor.py, and (2) Removed temporary review process files from the repository.
